news.title: BDR Pharma CMD's family buys apartments in Mumbai's Worli for Rs 81 crore
news.para: The performance in terms of stamp duty collection led by the heightened activity in premium and mid-income housing segments have also pushed the state exchequer’s revenue higher for several months.

news.title: China approves first batch of consumption-related REITs
news.para: The commercial real estate investment trusts (REITs) approved by the China Securities Regulatory Commission (CSRC) are backed by properties owned by SCPG Holdings Co. Ltd., Shanghai Xingxiumao Business Management Co. Ltd, and the commercial unit of China Resources Land.

news.title: Signa set to make further insolvency filings: Sources
news.para: Signa, controlled by an Austrian magnate but whose business is anchored in Germany, held talks with Elliott Investment Management to try to raise funds, according to one of the people, describing the company's scramble for cash.

news.title: Odisha RERA scraps land deal for violating registration norms
news.para: Sources said the landowner had created around 20 sub-plots of about an acre of land in Balianta area on the city outskirts without registering the bigger plot with ORERA and was selling them to multiple buyers.

news.title: With eye on sustainability, Goa government embarks on 3D-based urban planning
news.para: The agency has invited an expression of interest from interested firms for setting up procurement, implementation, and support of a 3D application for urban planning.

news.title: Nashik civic body to map properties using GIS
news.para: At present, the city has over 5.2 lakh properties on record with the property tax department. Moreover, properties that are still not on record will also be identified due to GIS mapping.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body fines 40% checked construction sites for air pollution
news.para: The facts came to the fore after checks by 32 dedicated squads formed by the Pimpri Chinchwad Municipal Corporation (PCMC) in 16 wards to take action in this regard.

news.title: Chennai: No green nod for resorts, villas in Mudaliarkuppam
news.para: Residents of Thazuthalaikuppam, a village in the neighbourhood, had filed a case seeking directions from the tribunal to demolish all 'illegal' constructions in Paramankeni and Mudaliarkuppam villages.

news.title: Himachal Pradesh sets up panel to study stone crusher units
news.para: The multi-sector committee, in its interim report submitted to the government, has submitted that along with the climatic change, the unscientific and illegal mining along the river beds was responsible for the natural calamity in the state that caused huge damage to life and property.

news.title: No metro link, Greater Noida West homebuyers hit the streets
news.para: The protest follows the PMO’s rejection of the detailed project report (DPR), along with the proposed skywalk linking DMRC’s Sector 51 metro station with Noida NMRC’s Sector 52 metro station. A fresh DPR will be made now.

news.title: Mumbai: Powai residents unite to oppose Brookfield's proposed mall, plan legal action
news.para: Canadian realtor Brookfield Properties which has bought over the commercial spaces of this largely residential complex has plans underway to construct a 400% larger commercial complex to house retail, office spaces, eateries and an entertainment zone, including multiplexes.

news.title: MHADA charging 18% interest a matter of concern: Maharashtra deputy CM
news.para: "The government will ask MHADA to put up a proposal; so that it could be brought at par with the BMC and we would have the same regulation in both the organizations," said Devendra Fadnavis, deputy chief minister of Maharashtra.

news.title: Kolkata: Licensed surveyors can now sanction building plans on land up to three cottahs
news.para: ​Under a new rule, the citizens having a small chunk of land — measuring up to 3 cottahs — can rope in an architect or an LBS and apply for a building sanction online to bypass unnecessary delays in getting the construction permit from the Kolkata Municipal Corporation.

news.title: GDA board clears master plan 2031, Ghaziabad set to get seven 'influence zones'
news.para: The three individual plans for Ghaziabad, Loni and Modinagar/Muradnagar were approved as one unified master plan for the entire Ghaziabad district.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body demolishes illegal colony in Giaspura
news.para: Assistant town planner (ATP - Zone C) Pardeep Sehgal and building inspector Paulparneet Singh said that on the directions of MC commissioner Sandeep Rishi, regular drives were being conducted to prevent illegal constructions in the city.

news.title: Panvel civic body allows property tax exemption for ex-servicemen
news.para: The waiver has been implemented in retrospective effect from April 1, 2023. According to PCMC, 55% of the total property tax is being collected under the head of general tax from the property holders.

news.title: Hyderabad: I-T seizes Rs 2 crore from King's Group of Companies
news.para: King's Group is a family business founded by Shanawaz, while Mohammed Zubairuddin, Mohammed Naseeruddin and Shaifuddin are directors. While I-T sleuths are investigating into Shanawaz's political links, he denied having any.

news.title: BMRCL set to start landwork for Bengaluru metro phase-III
news.para: ​In the first stage, 100 acres of land has been identified for building a depot and viaducts on some of the stretches of the corridor. A joint survey of the properties identified for acquisition is expected to start shortly, according to officials.

news.title: Gujarat SCDRC orders Sambhav Infrastructure to give possession of flats
news.para: The case involved five consumers, Naresh Balwani from Gandhidham, Mehulbharthi Goswami, Heena Khorasiya, Chakshu Suthar and Lalit Soni.

news.title: Bengaluru: Slum clearance sparks property tax surge proposal
news.para: ​The commission’s report, submitted to Chief Minister Siddaramaiah, proposed various measures, including the clearance of slums, which could necessitate increased contributions from taxpayers.
